comment.text: This translation key is used to display a notification when a room's external link has been renamed. The notification will show a before-and-after comparison of the old and new link titles. It appears in the UI for the "Room External Link" feature.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase 'renamed to' is not directly translated. 'olaraq dəyişdirildi' translates to 'was changed to', which doesn't convey the meaning of renaming as clearly as a more direct equivalent.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a more direct translation of 'renamed to', such as 'yenidən adlandırıldı' or 'adını dəyişdirərək'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English content uses <1>«{{...}}</1> consistently for the link titles. The Azerbaijani translation lacks the opening <1> for the second occurrence of the link title.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Add the opening <1> tag before «{{linkTitle}}» to match the English format:  <1>«{{linkTitle}}»</1>

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The verb 'renamed' should be translated as 'rinominato' rather than 'rinominato <1>«{{linkTitle}}»</1>'. The repetition is unnecessary and grammatically incorrect.
The closing angle bracket `>` is missing a closing quotation mark. It should be `</1>」

The phrase "이름이 ... 로 변경되었습니다" (im-i ...-ro byeon-gyeong-doeot-seumnida) literally translates to "... has been changed to..." which while understandable, sounds a bit formal and indirect for a notification about a link renaming. A more natural and concise phrasing would be preferable.  Consider something like "... 로 변경되었습니다" or "로 바뀌었습니다" (bwa-gyeot-seumnida).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider replacing "링크의 이름이 ... 로 변경되었습니다" with a more natural phrasing like "... 로 변경되었습니다" or "로 바뀌었습니다".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase "Link... renamed to..." is not perfectly captured by "Nazwa linku... została zmieniona na...".  "Nazwa linku" translates to "Name of the link", while the original emphasizes a *link* being renamed.  A more accurate translation would emphasize the link itself being renamed.
The formatting with <1> and «...» is maintained correctly in both languages.

The phrase "renamed to" is not accurately conveyed. "ලෙස" (lesa) literally means 'as' and doesn't directly translate the concept of renaming. A better translation for 'renamed to' would involve expressing the change in naming more explicitly.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider replacing "ලෙස" with a phrase like "නම් කරන ලදී" (naam karan ladi) or a more contextually appropriate synonym for 'renamed'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Bağlantı <1>«{{oldLinkTitle}}»</1> <1>«{{linkTitle}}»</1> olarak yeniden adlandırıldı' literally translates to 'Link <1>«{{oldLinkTitle}}»</1> <1>«{{linkTitle}}»</1> was renamed'.  A more natural Turkish phrasing would be something like 'Bağlantı <1>«{{oldLinkTitle}}»</1>, <1>«{{linkTitle}}»</1> olarak yeniden adlandırıldı' or 'Bağlantı <1>«{{oldLinkTitle}}»</1> yeniden <1>«{{linkTitle}}»</1> olarak adlandırıldı'.
